verses.text: And Jacob called unto his sons , and said , Gather yourselves together , that I may tell you \add that\add* which shall befall you in the last days.
Gather yourselves together , and hear , ye sons of Jacob ; and hearken unto Israel your father. \p
¶ Reuben , thou \add art\add* my firstborn , my might , and the beginning of my strength , the excellency of dignity , and the excellency of power :

Unstable as water , thou shalt not excel ; because thou wentest up to thy father’s bed ; then defiledst thou \add it:\add* he went up to my couch.\f + \fr 49.4 \ft thou shalt…: Heb. do not thou excel\f*\f + \fr 49.4 \ft he went…: or, my couch is gone\f* \p
¶ Simeon and Levi \add are\add* brethren ; instruments of cruelty \add are in\add* their habitations.\f + \fr 49.5 \ft instruments…: or, their swords are weapons of violence\f*

O my soul , come not thou into their secret ; unto their assembly , mine honour , be not thou united : for in their anger they slew a man , and in their selfwill they digged down a wall.\f + \fr 49.6 \ft digged…: or, houghed oxen\f*
Cursed \add be\add* their anger , for \add it was\add* fierce ; and their wrath , for it was cruel : I will divide them in Jacob , and scatter them in Israel. \p
¶ Judah , thou \add art he\add* whom thy brethren shall praise : thy hand \add shall be\add* in the neck of thine enemies ; thy father’s children shall bow down before thee.
Judah \add is\add* a lion’s whelp : from the prey , my son , thou art gone up : he stooped down , he couched as a lion , and as an old lion ; who shall rouse him up ?
The sceptre shall not depart from Judah , nor a lawgiver from between his feet , until Shiloh come ; and unto him \add shall\add* the gathering of the people \add be\add*.
Binding his foal unto the vine , and his ass’s colt unto the choice vine ; he washed his garments in wine , and his clothes in the blood of grapes :
His eyes \add shall be\add* red with wine , and his teeth white with milk. \p
¶ Zebulun shall dwell at the haven of the sea ; and he \add shall be\add* for an haven of ships ; and his border \add shall be\add* unto Zidon. \p
¶ Issachar \add is\add* a strong ass couching down between two burdens :
And he saw that rest \add was\add* good , and the land that \add it was\add* pleasant ; and bowed his shoulder to bear , and became a servant unto tribute. \p
¶ Dan shall judge his people , as one of the tribes of Israel.
Dan shall be a serpent by the way , an adder in the path , that biteth the horse heels , so that his rider shall fall backward.\f + \fr 49.17 \ft an adder: Heb. an arrow-snake\f*
I have waited for thy salvation , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*. \p
¶ Gad , a troop shall overcome him: but he shall overcome at the last. \p
¶ Out of Asher his bread \add shall be\add* fat , and he shall yield royal dainties. \p
¶ Naphtali \add is\add* a hind let loose : he giveth goodly words. \p
¶ Joseph \add is\add* a fruitful bough , \add even\add* a fruitful bough by a well ; \add whose\add* branches run over the wall :\f + \fr 49.22 \ft branches: Heb. daughters\f*
The archers have sorely grieved him , and shot \add at him\add*, and hated him :
But his bow abode in strength , and the arms of his hands were made strong by the hands of the mighty \add God\add* of Jacob ; (from thence \add is\add* the shepherd , the stone of Israel :)

\add Even\add* by the God of thy father , who shall help thee; and by the Almighty , who shall bless thee with blessings of heaven above , blessings of the deep that lieth under, blessings of the breasts , and of the womb :

The blessings of thy father have prevailed above the blessings of my progenitors unto the utmost bound of the everlasting hills : they shall be on the head of Joseph , and on the crown of the head of him that was separate from his brethren. \p
¶ Benjamin shall ravin \add as\add* a wolf : in the morning he shall devour the prey , and at night he shall divide the spoil. \p
¶ All these \add are\add* the twelve tribes of Israel : and this \add is it\add* that their father spake unto them, and blessed them; every one according to his blessing he blessed them.
And he charged them, and said unto them, I am to be gathered unto my people : bury me with my fathers in the cave that \add is\add* in the field of Ephron the Hittite ,

In the cave that \add is\add* in the field of Machpelah , which \add is\add* before Mamre , in the land of Canaan , which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the Hittite for a possession of a buryingplace.
There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife ; there they buried Isaac and Rebekah his wife ; and there I buried Leah.
The purchase of the field and of the cave that \add is\add* therein \add was\add* from the children of Heth.
And when Jacob had made an end of commanding his sons , he gathered up his feet into the bed , and yielded up the ghost , and was gathered unto his people.
